info.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 22 at 6:55AM EST until February 22 at 9:00AM EST by NWS Melbourne
info.description: ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM EST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Visibility one half mile or less in dense fog. * WHERE...Inland Volusia, Orange, Seminole, Osceola, Coastal Volusia, Inland Northern Brevard and Mainland Northern Brevard Counties. * WHEN...Until 9 AM EST this morning. * IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Areas of fog are spreading northward from northern Osceola County. Meanwhile, another area of fog and low stratus is spreading southward through northern Lake and Volusia Counties. Fog will continue to spread into the Orlando metro area for the next hour or so, before lifting between 8 and 9 AM.
info.instruction: If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of distance ahead of you.
